Experiment_Feedback: It was tricky to answer some of the initial questions because in terms of attitudes towards AI, it doesn't clarify if by AI they mean as it currently exists and is implemented in the world, or its potential if implemented and designed differently. Similarly, no distinction is made between generative AI and computational AI. This makes questions like "How exited are you by AI" difficult to answer because it depends on the specific type and whether or not I can consider hypothetical, ethical applications. AI that assists research and calculation is extremely useful and exciting for scientific growth, but generative AI that steals artwork and photos off the internet and generates soulless amalgamations of data points is incredibly unethical and potentially dangerous (such as with deepfakes).
